WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.699
Now we've had a couple of lessons, messages already, from this particular book.

00:00:04.699 --> 00:00:10.239
This is message number three and thankful for the Lord's leadership, I've mentioned

00:00:10.239 --> 00:00:15.800
in both of the previous messages from the book of James that this book is extremely

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:16.799
practical.

00:00:16.799 --> 00:00:22.440
In fact, the subject of trials was the subject in which we discovered last week as James

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:29.020
gets immediately into that subject and you find that as we study there in those verses

00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:34.299
of scripture from verses two down through verse number four, we understood their purpose,

00:00:34.299 --> 00:00:37.220
we also understood what they produce.

00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:42.819
And I would say this, the truth of verses two through four is something that every believer

00:00:42.819 --> 00:00:44.819
can benefit from.

00:00:44.819 --> 00:00:51.139
The reality that God has provided us with instruction so that we could understand when

00:00:51.139 --> 00:00:57.380
we fall into diverse temptations, those trials that would come your way, those trials that

00:00:57.380 --> 00:01:02.580
would come my way, those trials that we may face corporately as a body, that he says,

00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:04.819
my brethren, count it all joy.

00:01:04.819 --> 00:01:09.900
And we say this, that's not natural, that's not my natural response, it's not your natural

00:01:09.900 --> 00:01:15.260
response when there's a trial, but when we understand what God is doing and we understand

00:01:15.260 --> 00:01:21.419
that God has a purpose and he's trying to produce something in us, we can rejoice, we

00:01:21.419 --> 00:01:25.699
can have that joy in the midst of that trial.

00:01:25.699 --> 00:01:29.580
As we continue reading and we'll be looking this morning at verses five through eight,

00:01:29.580 --> 00:01:33.220
we find that there's quite a familiar verse within our text this morning.

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:37.580
In fact, verse number five of James chapter number one is a verse of scripture that's

00:01:37.580 --> 00:01:40.779
our memory verse for the month of January here.

00:01:40.779 --> 00:01:45.699
You see it on your calendar, it's been up on the screen and we're working on memorizing

00:01:45.699 --> 00:01:51.180
that verse and many of us have probably already memorized that verse at some point in our

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:57.180
lives and I would say this personally, that the truth of James 1.5 has been a great source

00:01:57.180 --> 00:01:59.580
of encouragement to me.

00:01:59.580 --> 00:02:04.300
And the promise and the truth that's contained therein, I would say this to you, that on

00:02:04.300 --> 00:02:10.639
countless occasions I've approached the Lord on the basis of this truth that we find in

00:02:10.639 --> 00:02:16.779
James chapter one and verse number five and I've humbly asked him to give me wisdom, acknowledging

00:02:16.779 --> 00:02:19.220
that I lack it and I need it.

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:23.020
We find the text of scripture beginning in verse number five of James 1.

00:02:23.020 --> 00:02:32.300
It says, if any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God that giveth to all men liberally

00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:36.940
and upbraideth not, and it shall be given him.

00:02:36.940 --> 00:02:42.179
But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering, for he that wavereth is like a wave of the

00:02:42.179 --> 00:02:45.139
sea driven with the wind and tossed.

00:02:45.139 --> 00:02:50.940
For let not that man think that he shall receive anything of the Lord, a double-minded

00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:55.220
man is unstable in all his ways.

00:02:55.220 --> 00:02:59.360
So we find that James, as we've started looking at these first eight verses as we've studied

00:02:59.360 --> 00:03:03.559
here now for three weeks, we find that he starts out by that introduction speaking about

00:03:03.559 --> 00:03:05.179
being a servant.

00:03:05.179 --> 00:03:11.539
We talked about, we really just hit it hard on our position as a servant and James understanding

00:03:11.539 --> 00:03:12.860
that position himself.

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:17.179
Of course, we understand that the Lord Jesus Christ, he humbled himself.

00:03:17.179 --> 00:03:20.339
He is a servant and what a joy.

00:03:20.339 --> 00:03:22.619
He is God, but he's a servant.

00:03:22.619 --> 00:03:27.259
We find that he came to minister not to be ministered unto and begin to read through

00:03:27.259 --> 00:03:32.100
the gospel accounts and begin to understand how James would have seen in the life of the

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:35.179
Lord Jesus Christ that servanthood.

00:03:35.179 --> 00:03:41.059
And now he writes, James a servant and how we too must acknowledge our position of being

00:03:41.059 --> 00:03:45.979
a servant of the Most High God and what a blessed position that is.

00:03:45.979 --> 00:03:51.500
He deals with the trials that these individuals were facing and because of the persecution

00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:57.979
and because of the scattering that arose after Stephen was martyred, we find that these Jewish

00:03:57.979 --> 00:04:03.020
believers had faced many trials and we too today, we face many trials.

00:04:03.020 --> 00:04:09.539
And he says, if any of you lack wisdom, if any of you lack wisdom, and the reality as

00:04:09.539 --> 00:04:15.380
he gets into this truth of wisdom, we can understand it within the context of the trials

00:04:15.380 --> 00:04:21.500
and how we need wisdom every day of our lives, but how we need God's wisdom when we're in

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:25.220
the midst of a trial, amen?

00:04:25.220 --> 00:04:31.380
And it's interesting when we understand the placing of this wonderful truth that is so

00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:36.339
familiar to many of us within the context there of dealing with trials.

00:04:36.339 --> 00:04:37.339
What is wisdom?

00:04:37.339 --> 00:04:43.500
Well, wisdom simply defined as the right use or exercise of knowledge.

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:51.220
We find that the knowledge and fear of God and sincere and uniform obedience to his command.

00:04:51.220 --> 00:04:55.179
We would find that James chapter 3, turn there just very quickly and we're not going to read

00:04:55.179 --> 00:05:01.779
all of the text, we'll preach through this in a few months, but you find in James 3 in

00:05:01.779 --> 00:05:06.299
these texts in verses 13 through 18, again I'm not going to read all of it, but we find

00:05:06.299 --> 00:05:10.540
that there's a contrast between the wisdom of the world and the wisdom of God.

00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:16.700
And he says in verse 17, but the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable,

00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:21.619
gentle, and easy to be entreated, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality

00:05:21.619 --> 00:05:24.320
and without hypocrisy.

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:28.059
We find that wisdom is the application of knowledge.

00:05:28.059 --> 00:05:33.899
If we read the book of Proverbs, you find in the book of Proverbs that God gives us

00:05:33.899 --> 00:05:37.820
much information with regard to wisdom.

00:05:37.820 --> 00:05:42.179
And there are some today when we speak about the subject of wisdom that they understand

00:05:42.179 --> 00:05:47.160
that worldly wisdom that James would speak of in the third chapter, but we're speaking

00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:51.899
about that wisdom that is from above, we're speaking about the wisdom of God.

00:05:51.899 --> 00:05:57.260
And we have people today that follow the same pattern that we'd find in Romans chapter 1

00:05:57.260 --> 00:06:02.279
in verse 22, professing themselves to be wise, they became fools.

00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:07.880
And we find this morning that the wisdom of God is contained within the word of God.

00:06:07.880 --> 00:06:13.320
God has given to us the complete canon of Scripture, and we can rejoice in that.

00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:17.359
I'm going to read a few verses from Proverbs 1, and then dig right in here to the book

00:06:17.359 --> 00:06:18.399
of James.

00:06:18.399 --> 00:06:23.040
And notice in Proverbs chapter 1, Solomon is writing under the inspiration of the Holy

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:24.359
Spirit of God.

00:06:24.359 --> 00:06:29.920
The Bible says in verse 1, the Proverbs of Solomon, the son of David, king of Israel,

00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:37.440
to know wisdom and instruction, to perceive the words of understanding, to receive the

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:43.359
instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity, to give subtlety to the simple,

00:06:43.359 --> 00:06:45.799
to the young man knowledge and discretion.

00:06:45.799 --> 00:06:51.760
A wise man, notice the description here, will hear and will increase learning, and a man

00:06:51.760 --> 00:06:59.200
of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels, to understand a proverb and the interpretation,

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:02.959
the words of the wise and their dark sayings.

00:07:02.959 --> 00:07:11.160
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of knowledge, but fools despise wisdom and instruction.

00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:16.839
As we look at the text this morning, I've simply entitled the message, We Lack Wisdom.

00:07:16.839 --> 00:07:18.320
We Lack Wisdom.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:22.600
And I hope that as we go through the message this morning, that each of us would truly

00:07:22.600 --> 00:07:27.640
come to that place in our lives that we acknowledge that we lack wisdom.

00:07:27.640 --> 00:07:29.600
I need God.

00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:31.079
You need God.

00:07:31.079 --> 00:07:32.799
We need God's wisdom.

00:07:32.799 --> 00:07:35.559
Life is too hard for us on our own.

00:07:35.559 --> 00:07:41.519
We understand that the Bible teaches us that without me, Jesus said, ye can do nothing.

00:07:41.519 --> 00:07:43.079
And I must abide in Him.

00:07:43.079 --> 00:07:47.920
I must understand the importance of walking in the Spirit so that I would not fulfill

00:07:47.920 --> 00:07:49.119
the lust of the flesh.

00:07:49.119 --> 00:07:54.000
And I understand, and I hope this morning that you understand as well, how desperately

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.000
we need God.

00:07:55.359 --> 00:08:00.920
If we're going to live a life that's pleasing to the Lord Jesus Christ, we need to live

00:08:00.920 --> 00:08:04.239
a life dependent upon the Lord.

00:08:04.239 --> 00:08:06.040
And we need His wisdom.

00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:10.760
I don't need the wisdom of the world, I need God's wisdom.

00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:14.279
And this morning, when we understand, as we look at the text of Scripture, I want you

00:08:14.279 --> 00:08:18.359
to notice first of all with me, there's something to recognize.

00:08:18.359 --> 00:08:22.880
Something to recognize, and really two thoughts within this idea of what is it that we're

00:08:22.880 --> 00:08:23.959
to recognize.

00:08:23.959 --> 00:08:28.880
Number one, we must recognize our lack of wisdom.

00:08:28.880 --> 00:08:36.200
It says in verse number five, here in chapter number one, if any of you lack wisdom, I would

00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:40.599
submit to you this morning that every one of us, we lack wisdom.

00:08:40.599 --> 00:08:42.440
We need God's wisdom.

00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:44.580
There are things that you will encounter.

00:08:44.580 --> 00:08:47.320
There are things that I will encounter in life.

00:08:47.320 --> 00:08:53.000
There are things that may come up tomorrow or this week that we need God's wisdom.

00:08:53.039 --> 00:08:59.359
But here's the problem, oftentimes we don't acknowledge, we don't recognize our lack of

00:08:59.359 --> 00:09:00.359
wisdom.

00:09:00.359 --> 00:09:01.359
You know what we do?

00:09:01.359 --> 00:09:02.359
We think we got it.

00:09:02.359 --> 00:09:03.400
We think we have it all figured out.

00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:07.919
We think we have the answers for all of the problems that we're going to face.

00:09:07.919 --> 00:09:11.159
And we think that we can handle it.

00:09:11.159 --> 00:09:16.140
Sometimes we get real confident in ourselves, in our own abilities, and we can handle these

00:09:16.140 --> 00:09:21.159
things and therefore we never ask for wisdom because we never acknowledge that we lack

00:09:21.159 --> 00:09:22.159
wisdom.

00:09:22.320 --> 00:09:26.239
You're not going to ask for something that you don't acknowledge that you lack.

00:09:26.239 --> 00:09:27.239
You say, that's deep.

00:09:27.239 --> 00:09:30.599
No, it's really actually simple.

00:09:30.599 --> 00:09:32.080
Very simple.

00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:37.000
If you don't acknowledge, you don't recognize this morning your lack of wisdom, you will

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:40.080
never ask God for wisdom.

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:46.039
So it's absolutely imperative that we recognize this morning that we lack wisdom.

00:09:46.039 --> 00:09:51.659
But notice also, not only do we recognize our own lack of wisdom, but we also must recognize

00:09:51.659 --> 00:09:54.419
God's abundant wisdom.

00:09:54.419 --> 00:09:57.260
I'm thankful that we serve the all-wise God.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:09:59.900
I'm thankful that our God not only does He

00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:01.860
we have all power, but he has all wisdom.

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:04.460
We use the word that he is omniscient,

00:10:04.460 --> 00:10:06.900
that he knows all things and he has all wisdom.

00:10:06.900 --> 00:10:08.620
And the Bible says here in verse number five,

00:10:08.620 --> 00:10:10.100
if any of you lack wisdom,

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:13.040
notice what it says, let him ask of God.

00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:15.620
And so we find that the instruction

00:10:15.620 --> 00:10:17.700
that James gives to the recipient,

00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:20.700
to us this morning as the reader of the book of James,

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:23.100
as we study this, that I lack wisdom,

00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:24.180
who am I to go to?

00:10:24.180 --> 00:10:26.900
I'm going to go to the one who has all wisdom.

00:10:26.900 --> 00:10:29.900
Let him ask of God.

00:10:29.900 --> 00:10:30.740
Why?

00:10:30.740 --> 00:10:32.260
Because God has all wisdom.

00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:34.780
And so we seek the face of God.

00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:37.380
I don't seek any other place.

00:10:37.380 --> 00:10:41.180
I seek God and I ask him to give me wisdom.

00:10:41.180 --> 00:10:43.140
You will never, as I mentioned a moment ago,

00:10:43.140 --> 00:10:45.660
ask for wisdom if you do not acknowledge

00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:47.060
your lack of wisdom.

00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:49.300
In like manner, if you don't recognize

00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:51.580
that God has all wisdom,

00:10:51.580 --> 00:10:55.300
you won't ask him for the wisdom that you need.

00:10:55.300 --> 00:10:58.420
I understand this morning that our God,

00:10:58.420 --> 00:11:02.680
he loves us and our God, he cares about us.

00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:06.540
I was rejoicing this morning in my personal prayer time

00:11:06.540 --> 00:11:08.560
of how much God cares about us

00:11:08.560 --> 00:11:12.900
and how much he loves us and how he desires to equip us

00:11:12.900 --> 00:11:14.820
and to give us what we need.

00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:16.840
And as we go through life,

00:11:16.840 --> 00:11:19.740
and I hope that you can relate this morning

00:11:19.740 --> 00:11:21.500
to the fact that we lack wisdom,

00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:23.700
but our God has all wisdom

00:11:23.820 --> 00:11:26.860
and he's willing to give it to us.

00:11:26.860 --> 00:11:29.540
And what a blessed truth that is.

00:11:29.540 --> 00:11:32.100
We find here that there's something to recognize,

00:11:32.100 --> 00:11:35.140
but number two, there's something to request.

00:11:35.140 --> 00:11:37.940
The Bible says, let him ask of God.

00:11:37.940 --> 00:11:40.440
By the way, aren't you thankful this morning

00:11:40.440 --> 00:11:43.540
for the direct access of every born again believer?

00:11:43.540 --> 00:11:46.080
I don't have to go through any other person.

00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:49.500
I don't have to do any kind of praying to some priest

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:50.980
or some other spiritual leader.

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:55.380
I have direct access to the throne of God.

00:11:55.380 --> 00:11:59.340
When Jesus Christ died on the cross of Calvary,

00:11:59.340 --> 00:12:00.660
lots of things happened,

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:02.460
but one of those things that happened

00:12:02.460 --> 00:12:06.420
was that the veil was rent in twain.

00:12:06.420 --> 00:12:08.460
And we find that Hebrews talks about

00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:11.900
that he's given us a new and living way,

00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:14.260
this direct access.

00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:15.820
The book of Hebrews says it this way,

00:12:15.820 --> 00:12:19.020
that we can come boldly before the throne of grace.

00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:22.660
Isn't that wonderful that we have that direct access?

00:12:22.660 --> 00:12:23.620
If you were to study,

00:12:23.620 --> 00:12:25.520
and we won't take time to even turn there,

00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:27.520
but in 1 Peter chapter number two,

00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:31.160
we find that there's the position of the believer,

00:12:31.160 --> 00:12:33.060
the fact that we are understanding

00:12:33.060 --> 00:12:34.580
the priesthood of the believer,

00:12:34.580 --> 00:12:37.900
that I can have that direct access.

00:12:37.900 --> 00:12:39.460
You understand in the Old Testament,

00:12:39.460 --> 00:12:41.980
you couldn't just walk into the Holy of Holies.

00:12:43.340 --> 00:12:44.760
Amen?

00:12:44.760 --> 00:12:48.140
And by the way, the high priest once a year

00:12:48.140 --> 00:12:50.020
was allowed to enter into the Holy of Holies,

00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:52.560
but he better follow the proper protocol

00:12:52.560 --> 00:12:55.000
before he entered into the Holy of Holies.

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:58.420
But you and I this morning, we have direct access.

00:12:58.420 --> 00:13:02.180
He says, let him ask of God.

00:13:02.180 --> 00:13:03.620
What a blessed truth.

00:13:03.620 --> 00:13:06.740
There's something for us to request this morning.

00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:08.740
And we find that there's some conditions

00:13:08.740 --> 00:13:11.380
that are given to us here in the text of scripture.

00:13:11.380 --> 00:13:12.440
He says, let him ask of God.

00:13:12.440 --> 00:13:15.300
We'll look at the rest of verse number five in just a moment,

00:13:15.300 --> 00:13:17.060
but look at verse number six.

00:13:17.060 --> 00:13:19.840
