00:13:20.700 --> 00:13:23.060
What does it mean to ask in faith?

00:13:23.060 --> 00:13:27.060
It means asking, believing that God is able.

00:13:27.060 --> 00:13:29.700
Believing that God has all wisdom

00:13:29.700 --> 00:13:32.380
and that God can give you the wisdom that you need,

00:13:32.380 --> 00:13:35.180
that he can give me the wisdom that I need.

00:13:35.180 --> 00:13:36.900
And we ask in faith.

00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:40.820
It's believing that God is who he said he was,

00:13:40.820 --> 00:13:42.380
who he said he is.

00:13:42.380 --> 00:13:45.580
And we find this morning that we ask in faith.

00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:49.420
And then he says this, nothing wavering.

00:13:49.420 --> 00:13:51.460
And think about the stability of the individual

00:13:51.460 --> 00:13:53.020
that has this confidence.

00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:56.860
They've recognized their own personal need for wisdom,

00:13:56.860 --> 00:13:58.340
that their lack of wisdom.

00:13:58.340 --> 00:14:00.040
They've also recognized the fact

00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:03.740
that the Lord God Almighty has all wisdom.

00:14:03.740 --> 00:14:08.740
And he's asking God, he's asking in faith, believing.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:11.940
And it says nothing wavering, nothing wavering.

00:14:12.940 --> 00:14:14.260
And then he goes on to describe,

00:14:14.260 --> 00:14:18.620
