00:14:22.340 --> 00:14:25.320
We begin to understand other portions of scripture

00:14:25.320 --> 00:14:27.940
that talk about that one that would waver.

00:14:27.940 --> 00:14:32.020
And he says that he that wavereth is like the wind,

00:14:32.020 --> 00:14:34.740
like the wave of the sea, driven with the wind and tossed.

00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:37.840
And no doubt, many, most of us have seen,

00:14:37.840 --> 00:14:41.340
we've been to a beach and we've seen those waves

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:44.500
that are tossed and the analogy is there for us.

00:14:44.500 --> 00:14:46.820
We find that the scriptures would teach about a tree

00:14:46.820 --> 00:14:49.060
that just wavers in the wind

00:14:49.060 --> 00:14:50.700
and just kind of goes back and forth.

00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:53.320
And God says, nothing wavering.

00:14:55.060 --> 00:14:58.460
Gives to us the idea of confidence,

00:14:58.460 --> 00:15:03.420
that I'm confident that God is going to answer the prayer,

00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:05.480
the prayer of faith.

00:15:05.480 --> 00:15:08.800
See, he says, for let not that man think

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:10.460
that he shall receive anything of the Lord.

00:15:10.460 --> 00:15:12.260
What man, the one that doesn't ask in faith,

00:15:12.260 --> 00:15:13.540
the one that's wavering.

00:15:13.540 --> 00:15:16.540
And then he says, a double-minded man is unstable

00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:17.780
in all his ways.

00:15:17.780 --> 00:15:18.860
Let me ask you this morning,

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:21.740
what do you really believe about God?

00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:23.020
What do we really believe about God?

00:15:23.020 --> 00:15:25.180
Do we really believe this morning

